org.apache.hadoop.yarn.server.timelineservice.storage

Class PhoenixOfflineAggregationWriterImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.service.AbstractService
      • org.apache.hadoop.yarn.server.timelineservice.storage.OfflineAggregationWriter
        • org.apache.hadoop.yarn.server.timelineservice.storage.PhoenixOfflineAggregationWriterImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, org.apache.hadoop.service.Service

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
 @InterfaceStability.Unstable
public class PhoenixOfflineAggregationWriterImpl
extends OfflineAggregationWriter
    Offline aggregation Phoenix storage. This storage currently consists of two aggregation tables, one for flow level aggregation and one for user level aggregation. Example table record: 
     |---------------------------|
 |  Primary   | Column Family|
 |  key       | metrics      |
 |---------------------------|
 | row_key    | metricId1:   |
 |            | metricValue1 |
 |            | @timestamp1  |
 |            |              |
 |            | metriciD1:   |
 |            | metricValue2 |
 |            | @timestamp2  |
 |            |              |
 |            | metricId2:   |
 |            | metricValue1 |
 |            | @timestamp2  |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |            |              |
 |---------------------------|
    For the flow aggregation table, the primary key contains user, cluster, and flow id. For user aggregation table,the primary key is user. Metrics column family stores all aggregated metrics for each record.

      • writeAggregatedEntity

        public org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.records.timelineservice.TimelineWriteResponse writeAggregatedEntity(TimelineCollectorContext context,
                                                                                                      org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.records.timelineservice.TimelineEntities entities,
                                                                                                      OfflineAggregationInfo info)
                                                                                               throws IOException
        Description copied from class: OfflineAggregationWriter
        Persist aggregated timeline entities to the offline store based on which track this entity is to be rolled up to. The tracks along which aggregations are to be done are given by OfflineAggregationInfo.
        Parameters:
        context - a TimelineCollectorContext object that describes the context information of the aggregated data. Depends on the type of the aggregation, some fields of this context maybe empty or null.
        entities - TimelineEntities to be persisted.
        info - an OfflineAggregationInfo object that describes the detail of the aggregation. Current supported option is OfflineAggregationInfo.FLOW_AGGREGATION.
        Returns:
        a TimelineWriteResponse object.
        Throws:
        IOException - if any problem occurs while writing aggregated entities.
